      "writtenOn": "2020-10-09T01:01:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "high-level: I think this impl could be simpler. Consider:\n- have a channel workC with struct{inv_to_fetch, channel_for_result}\n- have a buffered allResultC, of type `chan chan resultItem`\n- in the ByTimestamp callback, for each inv\n  - create a new channel for result, resultC\n  - send resultC to allResultC\n  - send workItem{theInv, resultC} to workC\n  \n- have N concurrent workers listening to workC. Each worker:\n  - reads the next item from workC\n  - fetches results, sends then to the workItem.resultC\n- final goroutine\n  - listens to allResultC. for each resultC\n    - receives from the resultC and adds to the response\n\n- have a global semaphore around RPCs\n",
      "revId": "a6655ac12ddbfa1b5d3935fa06c42bf6332e8fae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
