      "writtenOn": "2020-10-13T19:41:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve changed this to the approach you suggested.\n\nThe purpose of the accumulation is:\n- to sort their results together (results should be sorted by timestamp, then by testid, varianthash, resultid)\n- so that the page token is unambiguous. E.g. if the page token says ts:\u00272020-01-01T10:12:30\u0027, skip:\u00275\u0027 but there\u0027s two or more invocations at the same timestamp, skip:5 is only meaningful if we sort the results from all such invocations.\n\nI think this is likely not a problem with timestamps, but will be one with commit positions, so I am postponing this decision til that is implemented.",
